      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1769001556926,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The controlling terminal is also responsible for signal handling. \ni.e one of signal terminate (SIGINT) is Ctrl-C, when pressed on keyboard, no keystroke is usually delivered to the foreground program. \n\nThe terminal is operating in canonical mode will just omits the input byte sequence and \ninstead sends a SIGINT signal to the foreground program --> (or precisely the foreground process group)",
      "fontSize": 28.510224746484905,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The controlling terminal is also responsible for signal handling. \ni.e one of signal terminate (SIGINT) is Ctrl-C, when pressed on keyboard, no keystroke is usually delivered to the foreground program. \n\nThe terminal is operating in canonical mode will just omits the input byte sequence and \ninstead sends a SIGINT signal to the foreground program --> (or precisely the foreground process group)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
